The paper proposes a novel approach to graph-level representation learning using unsupervised and inductive methods. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), or computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms also supports these potential sub-categories.
